comments: Johnson (PHX) places his hands to Allen's (CLE) side along the perimeter and quickly removes them as marginal contact occurs.

Johnson (PHX) swipes forward and marginal contact occurs with Allen's (CLE) right arm after his gather. Ayton (PHX) moves alongside Allen's path and maintains a legal guarding position during Allen's driving shot attempt.
Moore (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and does not deliver the contact.
Booker (PHX) and Okoro (CLE) come together at the end of the drive and marginal contact occurs to Okoro's front as Booker naturally releases away.
Okoro (CLE) is drawn into the air toward Booker (PHX) on the pump fake and initiates body contact with Booker during his upward shooting motion.
Bridges (PHX) and Drummond (CLE) engage and disengage with one another as they move along the perimeter.
Drummond (CLE) and Ayton (PHX) make incidental arm contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Garland (CLE) places his left hand on Bridges' (PHX) left hip and marginal contact occurs as they move toward the sideline during rebounding.
Drummond (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in Booker's (PHX) path and does not deliver the contact.
Prince (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in Bridges' (PHX) path and does not deliver the contact as the defensive switch occurs.
Sexton (CLE) hooks his off-arm around Johnson's (PHX) right arm and initiates contact to Johnson's arm/side.
Moore (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and does not deliver the contact.
Drummond (CLE) and Moore (PHX) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another as Moore contests the driving shot attempt.
Moore (PHX) moves somewhat forward and marginal contact occurs with Sexton's (CLE) lower body during the driving shot attempt.
Drummond (CLE) rests his hands on Ayton's (PHX) backside and marginal contact occurs as Drummond releases away during rebounding.
Booker (PHX) and Okoro (CLE) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Sexton (CLE) commits a take foul on Bridges (PHX).
Booker (PHX) and Garland (CLE) come together during the inbound and marginal body contact occurs as they move over the screen.
Drummond (CLE) extends and delivers contact to Johnson's (PHX) side that dislodges him from position as the screen is set.
Moore (PHX) is jumping away from Prince (CLE) and would avoid Prince's right leg if he didn't extend it forward to initiate the marginal contact.
Drummond (CLE) extends his hands into Ayton's (PHX) back and initiates contact that dislodges Ayton from position, subsequently causing the ensuing contact between Ayton and Sexton (CLE).
Drummond (CLE) commits a take foul on Bridges (PHX).
Moore (PHX) engages and disengages with Okoro (CLE) during rebounding.
